'''Midge''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Chandrilan/Legends|native]] of a rural region of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Chandrila/Legends|Chandrila]]. By the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Midge was a [[Corporal/Legends|corporal]] in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and was newly recruited into [[General/Legends|General]] [[Crix Madine/Legends|Crix Madine's]] [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|commando unit]] as a field [[Technician/Legends|technician]]. The same year, Midge attended a briefing held on the Rebel [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], during which the Alliance discussed its plans to [[Battle of Endor/Legends|attack]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]].

==Biography==
[[File:Midgeh1.jpg|thumb|left|130px|Midge attends the mission briefing prior to the attack on the second Death Star.]]
The [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] Midge [[Chandrilan/Legends|hailed]] from a rural region of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Chandrila/Legends|Chandrila]]. At some point he joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] upon the inspiration of<ref name="CCG" /> the Alliance's [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander]]&mdash;and fellow Chandrilan<ref name="Mothma DB">{{DB|character|monmothma|Mothma, Mon}}</ref>&mdash;[[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]]. Midge became an Alliance [[Corporal/Legends|corporal]]<ref name="CCG" /> by the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. By that [[Time/Legends|time]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> he had recently been recruited into [[General/Legends|General]] [[Crix Madine/Legends|Crix Madine's]] [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|commando unit]] as a field [[Technician/Legends|technician]].<ref name="CCG" />

That same year,<ref name="NEC" /> Midge was present during a briefing held on the Rebel [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|Mon Calamari Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], during which Mon Mothma announced the Alliance's plan to [[Battle of Endor/Legends|strike]] at the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] in [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] over the [[Endor/Legends|moon of Endor]]. General Madine, who was in charge of planning the attack, announced that members of a [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]] led by General [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] would be sent to the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] to deactivate the [[SLD-26 planetary shield generator/Legends|SLD-26 planetary shield generator]] protecting the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], allowing Alliance [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] to destroy the battlestation's [[Hypermatter reactor/Legends|main reactor]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Personality and traits==
Midge was a fair-skinned man.<ref name="ROTJ" /> He was a self-taught [[Sniper/Legends|marksman]] and [[Scout/Legends|scout]]. Mon Mothma inspired him to join the Rebel Alliance.<ref name="CCG" />

==Equipment==
When he attended the briefing aboard ''Home One'', Corporal Midge wore the same uniform worn by other Rebel commandos at the briefing.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
Midge first appeared as a background Rebel character during the ''Home One'' briefing in [[1983]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. He was portrayed by an uncredited extra.<ref name="ROTJ" /> In [[July]] [[2000]], Midge was given a name and brief backstory in the ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

